<subSubSection id="D7D9EDF2CBC90DBABD267ED48584E58D" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="type">
<paragraph id="F0DB4AB3038B52F70545A2DD43D63581" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EBEFA64B6E8AB71FBFEA4E2E7EE21D18" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Marquesas Islands: Ua Huka: Summit of ridge near Hitikau, 
<taxonomicName id="3817C6E34BD31707E733AA9A1652244F" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tiliaceus">
<emphasis id="9AE86DC85C6976F1261A5D1F3E49B283" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Hibiscus tiliaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest, 820 m, 28 June 1997, S. Perlman, K. Wood, &amp; J.-Y. Meyer 15844 (holotype: PTBG-026355!; isotype: US!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DFFB5BBB974208FBEAAB981BCCEC5F4A" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="7BF6AB663CF345981E5B9D429259AAF5" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DD2333A0218E526E91A7EDE863247E87" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Shrubs 1-2 m tall; stems apparently few. Leaves opposite, borne on upper 2-5 nodes, broadly elliptic, 18-26 
<normalizedToken id="2EC57BB6AF18021F74B383EEB2A1C7F2" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
7-10 cm, lower surface densely ferruginous appressed pubescent, upper surface glabrate, irregularly dentate, the teeth variable in size, petiole 5-6.5 cm, ferruginous appressed to spreading pubescent. Flowers in cymes arising in the upper leaf axils, apparently 1-3 flowered, peduncle 0-2 mm, ca. 1-2 mm in diameter, pedicels up to 6 mm; calyx cylindrical-ellipsoid, white, plicate; corolla much longer than calyx; style up to 10 mm, flower parts otherwise unknown. Partly mature berries up to 14 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BAD3472DDB48DA6F161278DF7B4855B5" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="84558BAF496E9A5E5E1ADCBC1C9D39B4" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79FFE8FCFAB8E33F1B6273714D040842" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Marquesas Islands, rare, endemic to Hitikau summit area, Ua Huka, from 820-870 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4DB02B42AACE5E09ED81407B9ADC3F99" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="9F37B87BEDCA0D4E0B0A60EF68B23B91" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="054A810776BAC29C6E9B97BFBB445D72" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="DE784A6965C63D4A71FCD9590671DFA0" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="uahukaensis">
<emphasis id="F815C26644635EC3FA0AB3E507458D1E" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Cyrtandra uahukaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<taxonomicName id="35A6212766A7AEB24D6FDF37F9FFC6F1" authorityName="B. C. Stone" authorityYear="1968" baseAuthorityName="Hombr. &amp; Jacquinot ex Decne." class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Freycinetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pandanales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="impavida">
<emphasis id="B37DA866F6291CC06C7F290B2DEFF44B" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Freycinetia impavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName id="A9A7E42259EA6EA34B0CABD08DB41F7C" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tiliaceus">
<emphasis id="561249AF2989BB6033C2C2CEE57C4AD6" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Hibiscus tiliaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shrubland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F2ACF9400863F4794CC4F9CF358B1559" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="759130636BCE052F1D230EF6950A0612" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AFD116E45352623A57B54750A4ADB8E5" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">The specific epithet refers to the island of Ua Huka where the only known populations occur.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="341B5F4FDD468E0D4FDC6F23DE26293F" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="E33D1FE0A4A63A9E81EC6E9E3E688AB5" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="757FBF114D1E0358B1A3BC382F26D2E5" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
IUCN Red List Category: Critically Endangered CR B2a + 2b (i, ii, iii). B2: total area of occupancy less than 10 km2 (ca. 5 km2). B2a, a single population known; b (i-iii), habitat continuing decline inferred. The suitable habitat for 
<taxonomicName id="D0DCFA39D241EC9DEB5BD0B182DEC765" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="uahukaensis">
<emphasis id="4C5D8C5793F408B0FB152A69601E66E9" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Cyrtandra uahukaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Ua Huka (ca. 83 km2) is indicated as an endangered environment, threatened feral animals, and invasive plants, reducing the extent of the forest (
<bibRefCitation id="36DA0E672B5380A34E9F230ECDDABB5F" author="Florence, J" journalOrPublisher="Allertonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="226 - 237" refId="B8" refString="Florence, J, Lorence, DH, 1997. Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands. Allertonia 7: 226 - 237" title="Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands." volume="7" year="1997">Florence and Lorence 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5A23E38E78252F3BC14AC64B25F78762" author="Mueller-Dombois, D" journalOrPublisher="Springer, New York" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="444 - 460" refId="B14" refString="Mueller-Dombois, D, Fosberg, FR, 1998. Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands. Springer, New York: 444 - 460" title="Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands." year="1998">Mueller-Dombois and Fosberg 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8E2507EF5F3ACBBE3A7252DCCFFB339F" author="Meyer, J-Y" editor="Gillespie, RG" journalOrPublisher="University of California Press, Berkeley" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="332 - 338" refId="B13" refString="Meyer, J-Y, Salvat, B, 2009. French Polynesia, Biology. In: Gillespie, RG, Clague, DA, Eds., Encyclopedia of Islands. University of California Press, Berkeley: 332 - 338" title="French Polynesia, Biology." volumeTitle="Encyclopedia of Islands." year="2009">Meyer and Salvat 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5861B13EE5CFD1FB5D30322956AC111" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="specimens examined">
<paragraph id="2B064C127A00E920DBE73D4B5ACC72D2" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Specimens examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C16341467C4A1ECB06F1043C3F6BFE23" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="E42E816DAC0400524C089E1F80F888DC" bold="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Marquesas Islands. Ua Huka:</emphasis>
13 May 1918, Henry 7 (P); Hitikau summit region, large bowl-like plateau, 823-884 m, 
<geoCoordinate id="85B858E0E2B11EC263E904DFC2E78BF9" degrees="8" direction="south" minutes="54" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="22" value="-8.906111">8Â°54'22&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
, 139Â°31'66&quot;W, 28 June 1997, Wood 6380 (PTBG); Hitikau and the Vaikivi summit region, 790 m, 
<geoCoordinate id="BB170E21D3C4361B546AD377A11EEDB0" degrees="8" direction="south" minutes="54" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-8.9">8Â°54'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="3393542B96AD490E1A1CAA23325C5B38" degrees="139" direction="west" minutes="31" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-139.51666">139Â°31'W</geoCoordinate>
, 14-15 June 2004, Wood &amp; Perlman 10756 (PTBG).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2847DCC54F15D3F9D50A0F7DB018561F" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="9" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3C4515BBBECA38A9A314963D84F11C8B" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BB50D45791306668BF625B386CAFF16" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="9" pageNumber="42">
Little is known about this species as it has been collected only four times. None of the collections were preserved with any flowers, only young fruit. 
<taxonomicName id="31ECBCBBD96E2DD299AAAB93FA9D1B64" authorityName="W. L. Wagner &amp; Lorence" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="uahukaensis">
<emphasis id="319584EF24BE97C9EE4F1A6D129F7640" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
<pageBreakToken id="7631FF325D1DFEA5242664CA1C91B69F" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" start="start">Cyrtandra</pageBreakToken>
uahukaensis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the densely pubescent leaves and condensed inflorescences. It grows in the same area as 
<taxonomicName id="6E92C42671123391FBE1926F857B4AE6" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jonesii">
<emphasis id="3B71FD806D1004C8BF0F3406F6F804F8" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Cyrtandra jonesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and appears to be closely related. Their relationships and ecology should be studied as it seems atypical for two very closely related species of the genus to grow in near sympatry.
</paragraph>
